{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-23T00:00:00.000Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow and deny rules are fine-grained entries in Claude Code's settings files that tell the permission gate exactly which tool calls to auto-approve and which to block outright — sitting between the broad permission mode and the individual tool invocation."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Allow & Deny Rules Are"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Every time Claude Code wants to use a tool — edit a file, run a shell command, fetch a URL, call an MCP server — the request passes through a permission gate before it reaches the system. The gate consults three sources in order: deny rules, allow rules, and the active permission mode. Allow and deny rules are the data-driven layer in that stack, giving you surgical control over individual tools without changing the broad mode."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Allow rules"},{"type":"text","text":" mark specific tool calls as safe to run automatically. When a tool invocation matches an allow rule (and no deny rule), the gate lets it through without showing a prompt."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Deny rules"},{"type":"text","text":" mark specific tool calls as forbidden. When a tool invocation matches a deny rule, the gate refuses it immediately — regardless of what allow rules or the permission mode would otherwise say."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rule Syntax"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rules are strings in the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"permissions.allow"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"permissions.deny"},{"type":"text","text":" arrays in your settings file:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"permissions\": {\n    \"allow\": [\n      \"Bash(npm test)\",\n      \"Bash(npm run lint)\",\n      \"Bash(git diff*)\",\n      \"Read(src/**)\"\n    ],\n    \"deny\": [\n      \"Bash(rm -rf *)\",\n      \"Bash(git push --force*)\",\n      \"Bash(sudo *)\"\n    ]\n  }\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The pattern format is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"ToolName(argument_pattern)"},{"type":"text","text":", where:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ToolName"},{"type":"text","text":" is the exact tool identifier: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Read"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Edit"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Write"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"WebFetch"},{"type":"text","text":", and so on."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"argument_pattern"},{"type":"text","text":" is a glob-style pattern matched against the argument passed to that tool. For "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash"},{"type":"text","text":" this is the command string; for file tools it is the file path."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Omitting the parentheses (e.g. just "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"\"Read\""},{"type":"text","text":") matches all invocations of that tool, regardless of argument."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Glob wildcards: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"*"},{"type":"text","text":" matches any characters within a single path segment or command word; "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"**"},{"type":"text","text":" matches across multiple path segments. For Bash rules, the argument is the full command string, so "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(npm *)"},{"type":"text","text":" matches "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm test"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm run build"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm install"},{"type":"text","text":", and any other "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm"},{"type":"text","text":" invocation."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow Rules"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An allow rule auto-approves the matching tool call — the permission gate executes it without pausing to prompt. This is the primary tool for eliminating repetitive approval prompts on operations you already trust."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common allow rule patterns:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rule"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it auto-approves"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(npm test)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Exact "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm test"},{"type":"text","text":" invocation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(npm *)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Any "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm"},{"type":"text","text":" command"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(git diff*)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Any "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"git diff"},{"type":"text","text":" variant"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Read(src/**)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reading any file under "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"src/"},{"type":"text","text":" at any depth"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(pytest *)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Any "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"pytest"},{"type":"text","text":" invocation with arguments"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow rules work in any interactive permission mode — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"default"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"acceptEdits"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"autoApprove"},{"type":"text","text":". In "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"plan"},{"type":"text","text":" mode they have no effect because tools are never executed. In "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"bypassPermissions"},{"type":"text","text":" mode they are redundant because all tool calls are already auto-approved."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deny Rules"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A deny rule blocks the matching tool call outright. Claude Code reports that the action was denied and does not execute it. The defining property of deny rules is that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"deny always wins"},{"type":"text","text":": when a tool call matches both an allow rule and a deny rule, the deny rule takes precedence."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This makes deny rules the right tool for \"never do this under any circumstances\" constraints — protections you want enforced regardless of the active mode or allow list."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common deny rule patterns:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rule"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it blocks"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(rm -rf *)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All recursive delete commands"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(git push --force*)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Force-pushes to any remote"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(sudo *)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Any elevated-privilege command"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Write(/etc/*)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes to system configuration files"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(kubectl apply* --namespace prod*)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Production Kubernetes deployments"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deny rules remain effective in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"autoApprove"},{"type":"text","text":" mode, where the permission gate is otherwise permissive. This is one reason the recommended alternative to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"bypassPermissions"},{"type":"text","text":" for automation is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"autoApprove"},{"type":"text","text":" combined with a well-defined deny list."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where Rules Live"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow and deny rules are stored in the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"permissions"},{"type":"text","text":" key of any settings file in the standard hierarchy:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"File"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scope"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Typical use"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~/.claude/settings.json"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All projects on this machine"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Personal allow rules for your usual workflow (test runners, safe git ops)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/settings.json"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everyone in this repository"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Team-wide deny rules, project-specific allow rules"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/settings.local.json"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Your copy only (not committed)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Experimental rules you don't want to share yet"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rules from all applicable files are merged. When the same tool call matches a rule at both the user level and the project level, deny still takes overall precedence regardless of which file it comes from."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Evaluation Order"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The permission gate applies rules in a fixed sequence on every tool invocation:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Check deny rules."},{"type":"text","text":" If the tool call matches any deny rule, it is refused immediately. No further evaluation."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Check allow rules."},{"type":"text","text":" If the tool call matches any allow rule, it is auto-approved and executes without a prompt."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Fall through to the mode."},{"type":"text","text":" The active permission mode determines what happens next — prompt the user ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"default"},{"type":"text","text":"), auto-approve edits ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"acceptEdits"},{"type":"text","text":"), describe without executing ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"plan"},{"type":"text","text":"), or minimize prompts ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"autoApprove"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This means allow and deny rules are always consulted "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"before"},{"type":"text","text":" the mode has any say. A well-tuned allow/deny list therefore gives you predictable, deterministic behavior for the commands that matter most, while the mode handles everything else."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Mistakes"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Missing the wildcard on Bash rules."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(npm)"},{"type":"text","text":" matches only the bare string "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm"},{"type":"text","text":", not "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm test"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"npm run build"},{"type":"text","text":". Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(npm *)"},{"type":"text","text":" to cover all npm commands."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Expecting allow to override deny."},{"type":"text","text":" If "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(git push *)"},{"type":"text","text":" is in the allow list and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(git push --force*)"},{"type":"text","text":" is in the deny list, force-pushes are still blocked. Deny wins — always."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Overly broad allow rules."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(rm *)"},{"type":"text","text":" covers "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"rm -rf /"},{"type":"text","text":". Keep allow rules narrow; use deny rules to carve out dangerous variants from a wide pattern."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Putting team deny rules only in user settings."},{"type":"text","text":" Teammates who don't share your user settings file get no protection. Commit team-wide deny rules in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Forgetting that plan mode ignores allow rules."},{"type":"text","text":" In plan mode, tools are never executed, so allow rules have no effect. Switching to plan mode enforces read-only behavior, not security."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Define deny rules for destructive, irreversible, or production-touching commands "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"before"},{"type":"text","text":" you relax the permission mode. Deny rules are your safety net."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build your allow list incrementally. Run in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"default"},{"type":"text","text":" mode, observe which safe actions Claude repeats, then add allow rules for them. Don't guess at a broad allow list upfront."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Commit "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":" with project-wide deny rules so all contributors share the same protections automatically."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep user-level allow rules scoped to tools and commands that are safe across all your projects. A rule that makes sense for one project's test suite might be too permissive in another context."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pair broad allow rules with targeted deny rules. Allowing "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(git *)"},{"type":"text","text":" while denying "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(git push --force*)"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"Bash(git reset --hard*)"},{"type":"text","text":" lets read-only and safe git operations through while blocking the dangerous variants."}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow rules auto-approve matching tool calls, eliminating prompts for repetitive safe operations."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deny rules block matching tool calls outright; they take precedence over any allow rule or permission mode."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The evaluation order is fixed: deny → allow → mode default."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pattern format is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"ToolName(argument_glob)"},{"type":"text","text":"; omitting the parentheses matches all invocations of that tool."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Team-wide constraints belong in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":".claude/settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":" (committed to the repo); personal workflow shortcuts belong in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"~/.claude/settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The recommended approach to reducing prompt fatigue is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"default"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"acceptEdits"},{"type":"text","text":" mode combined with a carefully curated allow/deny list — not bypassing permissions entirely."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
